description*.en: Energy has corresponding intensive (size-independent) properties for pure materials. A corresponding intensive property is "Specific Gibbs Energy}, which is $\textit{Gibbs Energy} per mass of substance involved. $\textit{Specific Gibbs Energy" is denoted by a lower case g, with dimension of energy per mass (SI unit: joule/kg).
